HEADWORD: Plenish
<hw>Plen"ish</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Replenish</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To replenish.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>T. Reeve.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To furnish; to stock, as a house or farm.</def>
<mark>[Scot.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Plenishing</ent>⟦br⟧
